(1, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Mandatory Check Failed: UK customer without Provice state is getting FATAL Response', 'Scenario:Add a  UK Organization/Person Customer with out entity type & with the Minimum Requirement data from SalesForce\n1.Adding address without Province state type getting Error "Error in getting code type"\n2.Province state is not mandatory ', 3, 'High', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_19', '2015-09-04', '2015-09-08', '2015-09-08', '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', '[9/7/2015:Chandrika]Code is fixed and \nwill be deployed in build 2', 'It is working as expected \nUK customers with address (AddreeLineOne,City,country and Zip) is getting SUCCESS Response'),
(2, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Mandatory Check Failed: Other country customer address is getting FATAL Response', 'Scenario:Add a  other country Organization /Person Customer with out entity type & with the Minimum Requirement data from SalesForce\n1.Adding address without Province state type getting Error "Error in getting code type"\n2.Province state is not mandatory \n3.We added Province state type in the request and getting this error message "Insert of the following component failed: Address"', 3, 'High', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_20', '2015-09-04', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', '[9/7/2015:Visalakshi]Working in local as expected.\nNeed to check DB configuration and other\nvalues to make sure local is in sync with\ndeployed build\n[9/8/2015:Visalakshi]Standardization and Normalization\nis disabled which causes the issue of making Addr_line_One\nas null which leads to persistence exception', 'It is working as expected \nOther country customers with address (AddreeLineOne,City and country) is getting SUCCESS Response'),
(3, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a customer with XCustomerSubMarketType type other than 1000001 is getting FATAL Response ', 'Scenario:Add a  other country Organization /Person Customer with out entity type & with the Minimum Requirement data from SalesForce\n1.Add a customer with XCustomerSubMarketType != 1000001\nError message "CustomerSubtype or CustomerSubtypeValue is required or is incorrect"', 3, 'High', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_20', '2015-09-04', '2015-09-09', NULL, '2015-09-14', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', NULL, '1', 'Build - 3', '[9/7/2015:Visalakshi]Code table sheet contains different lang_tp_cd \nvalues for different custsubmarketType values.\nIn general lang_tp_cd value will be same for all\nthe code type values.\nNeed to confirm with Greg\n[9/9/2015:Visalakshi]Code table sheet updated\nwith same value of lang_tp_cd for different\nCustSubMarketType values', '9/14/2015 : Tested on Build 5 deployed on 11 sep 2015 and getting success response for submarkettype other than 1000001.tested for 1000081. Hence closing the defect'),
(4, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a customer with only AddressUsageValue and without type  is getting FATAL Response ', 'Scenario:Add a  other country Organization /Person Customer with out entity type & with the Minimum Requirement data from SalesForce\n1.Add a customer with AddressUsageValue as BILL_TO\nError message "The following is required: AddressUsageType"', 3, 'Normal', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_20', '2015-09-04', '2015-09-09', NULL, '2015-09-14', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', NULL, '1', 'Build-3', '[9/7/2015:Visalakshi]Code table sheet contains addressUsageValue\nas "BILL TO" but src data contains addressUsageValue\nas "BILL_TO".\nNeed to confirm with Greg\n[9/9/2015:Visalakshi]Code table sheet updated', '9/14/2015 : Tested on Build 5 deployed on 11 sep 2015 and getting success response for Addressusage value BILL_TO. Hence closing the defect'),
(5, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a customer with CreatedDate it is Persisting current timestamp in the database ', 'Scenario:Validate Source Identifier, Create_dt from source are  captured in MDM for EBS Account Number (Source System) Organization/Person Customer\n1.Add a customer with CreatedDate it is not getting persisted in the database \n2.Current timestamp is getting persisted', 3, 'Normal', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_22', '2015-09-04', '2015-09-10', NULL, '2015-09-14', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', NULL, '1', 'Build-4', '[9/7/2015:Visalakshi]This is the OOTB behavior of MDM.\nWhatever value we provide in the input,\nit persists current timestamp value into MDM.\n[9/10/2015:Visalakshi]Source created date is mapped to\nSince date in MDM.Code fixed and will be deployed in\nBuild 4', '9/14/2015 : Tested on Build 5 deployed on 11 sep 2015. As per the change in the requirement Source created date is being captured in SinceDate and CreatedDate with the current time stamp. Hence closing the defect. As this is working as expected, closing the defect.'),
(6, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a customer with XIdentificationIssueDate it is Persisting as date instead of persisting as timestamp in the database ', 'Scenario:Add a  other country  Organization Customer with status as ''active'' with all Minimum Requirement data + Identifier + Customer Extension Fields and with entity type as "Vendor"\n1.Add a customer with XIdentificationIssueDateit is Persisting as date instead of persisting as timestamp in the database \nExpected : 2015-08-10 00:00:00.000\nActual : 2015-08-10', 3, 'Normal', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_25', '2015-09-04', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', '[9/7/2015:Visalakshi]Code fixed and will be deployed in Build2', 'It is working as expected \nPersisting as timestamp : 2015-08-10 00:00:00.0'),
(7, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Person - Invalid Error Message Person without Firstname', 'MaintainParty -  Add a  other country  Person Customer with out Firstname & with other Minimum Requirement data from EBS Account Number\nError Message is not Correct:\n<ErrorMessage> GivenNameOne and LastName is required</ErrorMessage>\nExpected Error Message:\n<ErrorMessage> GivenNameOne is required</ErrorMessage>', 4, 'Low', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_9', '2015-09-07', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', NULL, 'It is working as expected \nthrowing error as "GivenNameOne is required"'),
(8, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Person - Invalid Error Message Person without Firstname + Last Name', 'MaintainParty -  Add a  other country  Person Customer with out Firstname + LastName & with other Minimum Requirement data from EBS Account Number\nError Message is not Correct:\n<ErrorMessage>LastName is required</ErrorMessage>\nExpected Error Message:\n<ErrorMessage> GivenNameOne and LastName is required</ErrorMessage>', 4, 'Low', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_11', '2015-09-07', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', NULL, 'It is working as expected \nthrowing error as "GivenNameOne and Last name is required"'),
(9, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a US customer without State is throwing an invalid error message', 'Scenario:Add a  US other country Organization Customer with out Address(State) & with other Minimum Requirement data\n1.Add a US customer address without State and with Zip code\nExpected : It show throw an prompt error message\nActual : It is throwing "ZipPostalCode and ProvinceState is required"', 3, 'Low', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_30', '2015-09-07', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', NULL, 'It is working as expected \nthrowing error as "ZipPostalCode and ProvinceState is required for US address"'),
(10, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a UK customer without Zipcode is throwing an invalid error message', 'Scenario:\nMaintainParty -  Add a  UK  Person Customer with out Address (postal code) & with other Minimum Requirement data\n1.Add a UK customer address without State and with Zip code\nExpected : It show throw "ZipPostalCode is required for UK customer" \nActual : It is throwing "ZipPostalCode is required" ', 3, 'Low', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_17', '2015-09-07', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', NULL, 'It is working as expected \nthrowing error as "ZipPostalCode is required for UK address"'),
(11, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Customer Per/Org - Add a customer without XCustomerMarketValue is throwing BTM ITxRxException', 'Scenario:\nMaintainParty -  Add a  other country  Organization Customer with out Market Type & with other Minimum Requirement data\n1.Add a customer address without Market Type is throwing BTM ITxRxException\nExpected : It show throw "Market Type/ value is required " \nActual : It is throwing "BTM ITxRxException occurred in Request and Response Framework"', 3, 'Normal', 'Closed', 'AddEntity_28', '2015-09-07', '2015-09-08', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'PQ', '1', 'Build - 2', NULL, 'It is working as expected\nthrowing error as "CustomerType or CustomerValue is required"'),
(12, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Contact - Add a contact is throwing "<ErrorMessage>Insert of following failed: ContactPerson</ErrorMessage>"', 'Scenario:\nMaintainParty -  Add a  other country  Organization Customer with out Market Type & with other Minimum Requirement data\n1.Add a Customer\n2.Add a Contact with Customer relationship\nExpected : Contact should get added successfully\nActual : <Throwable>com.dwl.bobj.query.PersistenceException: com.ibm.pdq.runtime.exception.DataRuntimeException: [pdq][10103][3.200.75] An error prevented the update operation from completing successfully.;  Caused by: com.ibm.db2.jcc.am.SqlIntegrityConstraintViolationException: DB2 SQL Error: SQLCODE=-407, SQLSTATE=23502, SQLERRMC=TBSPACEID=4, TABLEID=659, COLNO=31, DRIVER=3.67.27</Throwable>', 1, 'Critical', 'Closed', 'AddContact_1', '2015-09-08', '2015-09-09', NULL, '2015-09-08', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'Dev', '1', 'Build - 3', 'Changed fields custMarketType,\ncustSubMarketType\nand Entity type from not nullable to nullable\n fields\nwhich caused Persistence Exception', 'It is working as expected \nAble to Add a contact '),
(13, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Contact - Add a contact with phone is giving BTM response', 'Scenario:\nMaintainParty -  Add a  Contact with entity type as Contact,Contact Name, Role(Customer Relationship) & Phone \n1.Add a Customer\n2.Add a Contact with only phone\nExpected : It should get a SUCCESS Response \nActual : It is throwing "BTM ITxRxException occurred in Request and Response Framework"', 4, 'High', 'Closed', 'AddContact_2', '2015-09-09', '2015-09-10', NULL, '2015-09-14', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', NULL, '1', 'Build-4', '[9/10/2015:Visalakshi]Failing because of missed\nnull check. Code is fixed and will be deployed in\nBuild 4', '[9/14/2015:Lokesh]: Tested on the build 5 deployed on 11 sep and Contact is getting added with only phone number and as per the mapping document phone number table will be populated only when the standardization is enabled. Hence closing the defect'),
(14, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Contact - Add a contact with Relationship value as Renewal Contact is getting FATAL Response', 'Scenario:\nMaintainParty -  Add a  Contact with entity type as Contact,Contact Name, Role(Customer Relationship as CONTACT OF) & Phone\nSteps: \n1.Add a Customer\n2.Add a Contact with Customer Relationship as Renewal Contact\nExpected : It should get a SUCCESS Response \nActual : It is throwing "Relationship type or value is invalid"', 5, 'Low', 'New', 'AddContact_7', '2015-09-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-14 00:59:56', 'Dev', '1', NULL, '[9/10/2015:Visalakshi]Code table needs to be \nupdated with proper values', 'Need to update the code table values in CDRELTP'),
(15, 'Defect', 'PQ MDM ADD Contact - Add a contact with CreatedDate it is Persisting current timestamp in the database', 'Scenario:\nMaintainParty -  Validate Source Identifier, Create_dt from source are  captured for the Contact in MDM\nSteps:  \n1.Add a Customer\n2.Add a Contact with createdDate it is persisting current time stamp \nExpected : CreatedDate should persist the timestamp from request\nActual : It is Persisting current time stamp', 3, 'Normal', 'Closed', 'AddContact_5', '2015-09-09', '2015-09-10', NULL, '2015-09-14', '2016-01-14 00:59:56', NULL, '1', NULL, '[9/10/2015:Visalakshi]Source created date is\nmapped to Since date in MDM.\nCode is fixed and will be deployed in Build 4\n9/14/2015 : Tested on Build 5 deployed on 11 sep 2015. As per the change in the requirement Source created date is being captured in SinceDate and CreatedDate with the current time stamp. Hence closing the defect. As this is working as expected, closing the defect.', NULL),
